\title{Conjugation forms an equivalence relation}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-16}
\taxon{remark}

\p{Taking [[gr-002B]] together with [[gr-0029]] and [[gr-002A]] means that the predicate "is conjugate to" forms an [[nst-0011]].}

\p{Consequently, we will be able to say "#{a} and #{b} are conjugate" instead of caring especially about the ordering of arguments to the predicate.}